    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="1242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1700</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-11T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1525. My No. 1412,<note n="1" xml:id="d1242fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_929">p. 929</ref>.</note> May
                    24. I am unofficially informed by Foreign Office that French Government agrees
                    to delivery of hospital supplies for Jerusalem under certain conditions.
                    American Consul at Alexandria should consult with Admiral de Spitz, in command
                    of blockading squadron, as to manner of debarkation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
